body_html:
@asimshankar
Thanks for your reply!

Yeah, there is no protobuf symbols in libtensorflow_cc.so and therefore I install the protobuf-3.4 (same as the protobuf used in tensorflow-1.5) and linked it into my test program. And I compile my test program by

g++ test.cc -I /usr/local/tensorflow/include -L /usr/local/tensorflow/lib -ltensorflow_cc -lprotobuf

where I have install the tensorflow in /usr/local/tensorflow.

body:
@asimshankar 
Thanks for your reply!

Yeah, there is no protobuf symbols in `libtensorflow_cc.so` and therefore I install the protobuf-3.4 (same as the protobuf used in tensorflow-1.5) and linked it into my test program. And I compile my test program by
```shell
g++ test.cc -I /usr/local/tensorflow/include -L /usr/local/tensorflow/lib -ltensorflow_cc -lprotobuf
```
where I have install the tensorflow in `/usr/local/tensorflow`.
